This project is a visually engaging infographic that introduces key aspects of digital literacy for students.
It explains what digital literacy means, highlights useful tools like Google Workspace and Canva for learning
and collaboration, and outlines essential internet safety practices such as strong passwords and verifying sources.
The design uses clear sections, icons, and color coding to make information easy to understand at a glance.
It also emphasizes building a professional online presence and following proper email etiquette.
Overall, the infographic aims to enhance students’ awareness, productivity, and responsible behavior in the
digital world through simple, structured, and visually appealing content.
